cpp-pinyin
------------------------------------------
cpp-pinyin is a lightweight Chinese/Cantonese to Pinyin library.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libcpp-pinyin-devel-1.0.2-1bl1
  libcpp-pinyin1-1.0.2-1bl1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/wolfgitpr/cpp-pinyin

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/wolfgitpr/cpp-pinyin/archive/refs/tags/1.0.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack cpp-pinyin-1.0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./cpp-pinyin-1.0.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/cpp-pinyin-1.0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/cpp-pinyin-1.0.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcpp-pinyin1-1.0.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcpp-pinyin-devel-1.0.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

